{"questionId":"7508","questionHtml":"<p>The escape speed for the Earth is <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"v\">\n  <mi>v</mi>\n</math></span><sub>esc</sub>. Planet X has half the density of the Earth and twice the&nbsp;radius. What is the escape speed for planet X?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>A.&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{v_{{\\text{esc}}}}}}{2}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>v</mi>\n          <mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mtext>esc</mtext>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{v_{{\\text{esc}}}}}}{{\\sqrt 2 }}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>v</mi>\n          <mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mtext>esc</mtext>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </msqrt>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp; <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"v\">\n  <mi>v</mi>\n</math></span><sub>esc</sub></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\sqrt 2 }\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msqrt>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msqrt>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"v\">\n  <mi>v</mi>\n</math></span><sub>esc</sub></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>D</p>","meta":{"questionId":"7508","referenceCode":"18N.1.HL.TZ0.32","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"The escape speed for the Earth is v esc. Planet X has half the density of the Earth and twice the radius. What is the es